.TH SPELLCHECK "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
spellcheck \- Script to check spelling
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spellcheck
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,FILE\/\fR|[\fI\,WORD\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B spellcheck
is a script for checking spelling in files or individual words. It provides batch processing, interactive mode, dictionary management, and multi-language support.
.PP
The script uses aspell or hunspell as the backend spell checker.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B spellcheck document.txt
Check spelling in a file
.TP
.B spellcheck "awkward"
Check spelling of a single word
.TP
.B echo "text" | spellcheck
Check spelling from stdin
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/spellcheck/settings.conf
User configuration file for spellcheck preferences
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/spellcheck/dictionary
Custom dictionary for additional words
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error or spelling errors found
.TP
.B 3
Spell checker not found
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Supports batch processing of multiple files
.IP \(bu 2
Interactive mode for corrections
.IP \(bu 2
Multi-language support
.IP \(bu 2
Custom dictionary management
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B Required (one of):
.RS
